Sentencas: The performance, long-term durability, and thermal cycling tolerance of metal supported solid oxide fuel cells (MS-SOFCs) operating with natural gas reformate fuels is assessed.
Titulo: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operating with reformed natural gas and sulfur

Sentencas: Symmetric MS-SOFCs with composite SDC-Ni anode catalysts and PrOx cathode catalysts are operated with simulated natural gas steam-reformate and partial-oxidation-reformate fuels with 1 ppm and 5 ppm of sulfur.
Titulo: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operating with reformed natural gas and sulfur

Sentencas: Cells are operated for 1000 h with initial degradation rates similar to humidified H-2, and initial performance differences attributed to the lower H-2 concentration in reformate fuels.
Titulo: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operating with reformed natural gas and sulfur

Sentencas: Additionally, cells tolerate many aggressive thermal cycles with sulfur present, with minimal impact on performance.
Titulo: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operating with reformed natural gas and sulfur

Sentencas: Post mortem analysis suggests that Ni particle coarsening and Cr deposition are sources of degradation, while carbon and sulfur deposition are not observed.
Titulo: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operating with reformed natural gas and sulfur

Sentencas: Overall, MS-SOFCs operate successfully with reformed natural gas.(c) 2022 The Author(s).
Titulo: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operating with reformed natural gas and sulfur
